TITLE: Chinese authorities apologize for COVID-19 break-ins
SUMMARY: Chinese leaders show remorse on behalf of police and health workers who have broken into homes in order to enforce the country's COVID-19 policies. Break-ins were seen on social media

TITLE: European heat wave: UK breaks records
SUMMARY: An oppressive heat wave in Europe has led to record-shattering temperatures in the United Kingdom. Forecasters said it would get even hotter there on Tuesday.

TITLE: California man faces execution in Iran for being a journalist
SUMMARY: Three dictators from Russia, Turkey and the Islamic Republic meet in Iran's capital Tehran today to carve up the Mideast as a California man is slated to be murdered for his journalism in Tehran.

TITLE: Africa: the new ground zero for jihadi terror groups, experts say
SUMMARY: Experts warn that Africa has become the latest hotspot for jihadi terror groups. The continent has become a battleground for a variety of ISIS and al-Qaeda-inspired terrorist groups.

TITLE: Pakistan resumes search for 29 missing after boat capsized
SUMMARY: Authorities are searching for passengers after a boat carrying nearly 100 people capsized in the Indus River in Hyderabad, Pakistan.

TITLE: US affirms Greek security in face of Turkish belligerence
SUMMARY: Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin reiterated the United States' support of Greece on Monday in the face of increasing tensions between Greece and Turkey over the Aegean Sea.

TITLE: Some China areas extend their lockdowns and testing amid COVID-19 omicron variant spread
SUMMARY: Major Chinese cities, including Shanghai, have re-implemented mass testing sites and lockdown measures as COVID-19 cases continue to rise across the country.

TITLE: Wild monkeys steal infant, throw child off roof in tragic attack
SUMMARY: A gang of monkeys killed a newborn baby in India on Friday, when the they snatched him from his parents and threw him off a roof terrace as family members looked on in horror.

TITLE: Brazilian FM: 'Give peace a chance,' discusses Brazil's relations with the US, China, Russia
SUMMARY: Brazilian Foreign Minister, Carlos Franca sat down with Fox News Digital to discuss his country's foreign policy and its role on the world stage. Franca lauded his country's close relationship with China.

TITLE: Pro-Russia separatists capture US Air Force vet in Ukraine: brother
SUMMARY: Sele Murekezi says his brother, U.S. Air Force veteran Suedi Murekezi was captured by pro-Russian separatists in the Ukrainian region known as the Donetsk People's Republic.

TITLE: Iran sanctions 61 more Americans as nuclear talks hit impasse
SUMMARY: Iran announced sanctions on 61 Americans Saturday, including former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo, after they backed the Iranian dissident group, Mujahideen-e-Khalq (MEK).

TITLE: Shooting at tourist hotspot on Spain's coast leaves 1 dead, 5 injured
SUMMARY: At least five people were wounded in a Marbella, Spain nightclub early Monday morning, according to police. The gunman is among those who were wounded.

TITLE: Zelenskyy fires head of Ukraine Security Service, announces hundreds of criminal treason cases
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said his country is undergoing a "self-purification" process as he looks to root out officials and law enforcement officers who are guilty of corruption and treason.

TITLE: Khamenei adviser says Tehran 'capable of building nuclear bomb,' Al Jazeera reports
SUMMARY: A day after President Joe Biden ended his Middle East trip, senior advisor Kamal Kharrazi said that Iran has the technology to build a nuclear bomb.

TITLE: Brittney Griner guilty plea possible 'gamble' to speed up Russia exit: expert
SUMMARY: Brittney Griner pleaded guilty to drug charges, but some suggest that her plea is merely an attempt to make herself eligible for a prisoner swap so she can leave Russia sooner.

TITLE: Dutch farmer revolt against harsh climate law just the beginning, experts say: 'There will be unrest all over'
SUMMARY: Western government should be prepared for more widespread protests and pushback if they pursue climate policies that harm consumers, experts interviewed by Fox News Digital said.

TITLE: China floods leave at least 12 dead, thousands evacuated
SUMMARY: Flash floods in China have least at least a dozen dead and endangered the lives of thousands as parts of the country experience soaring temperatures amid a heat wave.

TITLE: Ukrainian cargo plane crashes over Greece: Residents were 'hearing explosions' for hours
SUMMARY: Loud explosions were heard hours after a cargo plane operated by a Ukrainian carrier crashed near the city of Kavala, Greece. Aviation authorities said the plane was carrying mostly explosives.

TITLE: Western Europe ravaged by wildfires as hundreds reported dead from heat wave
SUMMARY: Extreme heat throughout Europe has sparked wildfires in France, Portugal and Spain, prompting mass evacuations.

TITLE: China may seek greater role in Haiti as UN Security Council extends political mission
SUMMARY: Some speculate China has increased involvement in Haiti in hopes of influencing any new administration to rescind its recognition of Tawian as an independent state.
